## 5. Static Form Anatomy Contract

Frontend stores one static array of forms with shape:

```ts
type FormAnatomy = {
  code: string; // A..N (13 + 1 set)
  title: { en: string; hi: string };
  order: number;
  questions: Question[];
};

type Question = {
  qid: string;
  ord: number;
  title: { en: string; hi: string };
  type: "boolean" | "options" | "text" | "number" | "multi_number" | "matrix";
  uom?: { en: string; hi: string };
  options?: Array<{ value: string; label: { en: string; hi: string } }>;
  parentId?: string;
  triggerValue?: string;
};
```

This is the single source of truth for rendering and conditional visibility.

## 6. Core Product Flow

### Step 1: Create or select session

- Landing page shows session toolbar.
- User either creates a session or selects an existing session.
- Selected session becomes active UI context.

### Step 2: Open form card and create empty entry

- Landing page shows 13 + 1 form cards.
- Clicking card shows entries list for that `formCode`.
- `Create New Entry` creates an empty session entry draft in backend.

### Step 3: Fill and save

- New draft redirects to:
  - `/fill/:sessionID/:entryID/section-a`
- Existing entry redirects to:
  - `/fill/:sessionID/:entryID/section-a/edit`
- UI renders anatomy from static JSON and computes visible questions.
- Saves happen via patch/update API calls; user can resume later.

## 7. Frontend Route Map

| Route | Purpose |
| --- | --- |
| `/` | Session toolbar + 13 + 1 form cards |
| `/fill/:sessionID/:entryID/:section` | Fill draft flow |
| `/fill/:sessionID/:entryID/:section/edit` | Edit existing entry flow |

## 8. Backend API Contract Used by Frontend

### Sessions

| Method | URL | Use |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `POST` | `/api/v1/sessions` | Create session |
| `GET` | `/api/v1/sessions` | Session listing |
| `GET` | `/api/v1/sessions/:id` | Session detail validation |

### Session entries

| Method | URL | Use |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `GET` | `/api/v1/sessions/:id/entries?formCode=A` | List entries under one card |
| `POST` | `/api/v1/sessions/:id/entries` | Create empty draft entry |
| `GET` | `/api/v1/sessions/:id/entries/:entryId` | Load one entry |
| `PATCH` | `/api/v1/sessions/:id/entries/:entryId` | Save partial answers |
| `POST` | `/api/v1/sessions/:id/entries/:entryId/submit` | Mark submitted |
| `DELETE` | `/api/v1/sessions/:id/entries/:entryId` | Soft delete |

All session-entry routes are open in local team mode for this phase.

## 9. HTTP and State Management

- axios base URL: `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` (default `http://localhost:3001`)
- no auth-header interceptor is required in this phase
- TanStack Query keys:
  - `['sessions']`
  - `['session', sessionId]`
  - `['entries', sessionId, formCode]`
  - `['entry', sessionId, entryId]`
- mutations invalidate affected keys

## 10. Conditional Rendering Logic

```ts
function getVisibleQuestions(questions: Question[], answers: Record<string, unknown>) {
  return questions
    .filter(q => !q.parentId || answers[q.parentId] === q.triggerValue)
    .sort((a, b) => a.ord - b.ord);
}
```

Rules:
- No nested expression engine.
- Parent change recomputes visibility instantly.
- Hidden question answers may be preserved unless explicitly cleared by section policy.

## 11. UI Requirements

- Top-level landing has:
  - session create/select toolbar
  - 13 + 1 card grid
- Each card opens entry list view
- Entry list has `Create New Entry`
- Fill page supports:
  - autosave feedback
  - resume support
  - bilingual labels
  - progress indicator (`answered / visible`)

## 12. Out of Scope

- Backend-managed dynamic forms
- form seed upload flows
- share slug based public form routes
- cross-device merge workflow (this phase)
- analytics/reporting layer
- role/auth frameworks beyond edit key

## 13. Build Order

1. Finalize frontend PRD and static anatomy conventions.
2. Build session toolbar UX on landing.
3. Build 13 + 1 form cards from static anatomy metadata.
4. Build entry list by form card.
5. Wire `Create New Entry` + redirects.
6. Build fill/edit pages using static anatomy + conditional logic.
7. Add autosave and submit transitions.
8. Add error/retry states and polish.

## 14. Definition of Done

- User can create/select session from landing.
- User can open any form card and view its entries.
- `Create New Entry` creates backend draft and routes correctly.
- User can partially fill, save, leave, and resume.
- UI is fully driven by static anatomy JSON.
- Session and session-entry routes function without edit-key/auth headers.
- Local checks pass (`typecheck`, `lint`, `build`).

